#Operating system introduction


computer system components: 1. hardware: CPU, memory, I/O device
                            2. operating system 
                            3. application program 
                            4. user
          fundamental goal: excution of program, to make solving user program easier
          
operating system: software that manages a computer's hardware
            role- provide a basis for application program (allocate resource, control program)
                  act as an intermediary between the computer user and the computer hardware

constitution of OS: kernel- program running all times on the computer
                    system program- aid in managing
                    middleware- a set of software frameworks that provide additional services to application developer

<-> application program: includes all programs not associated with the operation of the system

                   

